&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Climate Change Adaptation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Climate Change Adaptation&lt;/strong&gt; refers to measures taken to adjust to the current or expected effects of climate change in order to minimize harm or exploit beneficial opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The construction of &lt;strong&gt;sea walls&lt;/strong&gt; and elevation of buildings specifically addresses the impacts of &lt;strong&gt;rising sea levels&lt;/strong&gt;, which are a direct consequence of climate change. These are preventive actions to safeguard infrastructure and human lives.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adaptation strategies are often localized and cater to the specific challenges posed by climate change, such as floods, droughts, or temperature increases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The goal of adaptation is to build &lt;strong&gt;resilience&lt;/strong&gt; in communities, economies, and ecosystems, allowing them to cope with the adverse effects of climate change.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This approach differs from mitigation, which focuses on reducing the causes of climate change, such as greenhouse gas emissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Climate Change Mitigation:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mitigation involves efforts to reduce or prevent the emission of greenhouse gases (GHGs) that contribute to global warming.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Examples include switching to renewable energy sources like solar or wind, increasing energy efficiency, and adopting sustainable transportation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This strategy aims to address the root cause of climate change rather than its effects.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For instance, the Paris Agreement focuses on mitigation by setting targets for reducing global GHG emissions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Carbon Sequestration:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It refers to the process of capturing and storing atmospheric carbon dioxide (CO2) to reduce its concentration in the atmosphere.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Natural methods include afforestation, reforestation, and soil management, while technological solutions include carbon capture and storage (CCS).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Carbon sequestration is a key component of climate change mitigation strategies, aimed at offsetting emissions from industrial processes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Geoengineering:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Geoengineering involves large-scale interventions in Earth&amp;#39;s natural systems to counteract climate change.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Examples include solar radiation management (reflecting sunlight back into space) and ocean fertilization to enhance carbon capture by marine ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These methods are controversial due to their potential unintended consequences and ethical concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of Climate Change Adaptation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Constructing flood barriers in coastal cities prone to rising sea levels.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Implementing drought-resistant crops in regions experiencing water scarcity due to climate changes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Developing early warning systems for extreme weather events such as hurricanes or heatwaves.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Retrofitting infrastructure to withstand extreme weather conditions, such as stronger buildings to resist cyclones.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rising Sea Levels:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sea levels have been rising globally due to melting ice caps and glaciers, as well as the thermal expansion of seawater caused by global warming.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;According to the &lt;strong&gt;Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC)&lt;/strong&gt;, global sea levels could rise by 0.3 to 1 meter by 2100.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This poses threats to low-lying and coastal areas, leading to increased flooding, erosion, and loss of habitats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Adaptation Efforts:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;UN Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC)&lt;/strong&gt; emphasizes the need for adaptation measures alongside mitigation strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Programs like the &lt;strong&gt;Global Environment Facility (GEF)&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;Green Climate Fund (GCF)&lt;/strong&gt; provide financial support for adaptation projects in developing countries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Several nations, including the Netherlands, have implemented large-scale adaptation projects such as flood management systems and sustainable urban planning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

