&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Model Women-Friendly Gram Panchayats Initiative to be Launched at National Convention on 5th March 2025, in New Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;3235&quot; data-start=&quot;3035&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3071&quot; data-start=&quot;3041&quot;&gt;Ministry of Panchayati Raj&lt;/strong&gt; will launch the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3136&quot; data-start=&quot;3088&quot;&gt;Model Women-Friendly Gram Panchayats (MWFGP)&lt;/strong&gt; initiative at a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3176&quot; data-start=&quot;3153&quot;&gt;National Convention&lt;/strong&gt; on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3198&quot; data-start=&quot;3180&quot;&gt;5th March 2025&lt;/strong&gt; at &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3219&quot; data-start=&quot;3202&quot;&gt;Vigyan Bhawan&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3234&quot; data-start=&quot;3221&quot;&gt;New Delhi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;3419&quot; data-start=&quot;3236&quot;&gt;This initiative aims to establish at least &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3324&quot; data-start=&quot;3281&quot;&gt;one Model Women-Friendly Gram Panchayat&lt;/strong&gt; in each district, focusing on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3375&quot; data-start=&quot;3355&quot;&gt;gender-sensitive&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3408&quot; data-start=&quot;3380&quot;&gt;girl-friendly governance&lt;/strong&gt; practices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;3799&quot; data-start=&quot;3420&quot;&gt;Key highlights include:
	&lt;ul data-end=&quot;3799&quot; data-start=&quot;3448&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3552&quot; data-start=&quot;3448&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;3474&quot; data-start=&quot;3450&quot;&gt;Virtual inauguration&lt;/strong&gt; of training for &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3518&quot; data-start=&quot;3491&quot;&gt;Elected Representatives&lt;/strong&gt; and officials of Gram Panchayats.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3612&quot; data-start=&quot;3555&quot;&gt;Launch of a &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3593&quot; data-start=&quot;3569&quot;&gt;Monitoring Dashboard&lt;/strong&gt; to track progress.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3708&quot; data-start=&quot;3615&quot;&gt;Presentations on the concept and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3668&quot; data-start=&quot;3650&quot;&gt;best practices&lt;/strong&gt; for &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3707&quot; data-start=&quot;3673&quot;&gt;Women-Friendly Gram Panchayats&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3799&quot; data-start=&quot;3711&quot;&gt;Screening of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3750&quot; data-start=&quot;3726&quot;&gt;Informational Videos&lt;/strong&gt; showcasing successful initiatives in Panchayats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;4015&quot; data-start=&quot;3800&quot;&gt;Following the National Convention, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3859&quot; data-start=&quot;3837&quot;&gt;Mahila Gram Sabhas&lt;/strong&gt; will be organized across India on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3912&quot; data-start=&quot;3894&quot;&gt;8th March 2025&lt;/strong&gt;, coinciding with &lt;strong data-end=&quot;3959&quot; data-start=&quot;3930&quot;&gt;International Women&amp;rsquo;s Day&lt;/strong&gt;, marking the grassroots-level launch of the initiative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bay of Bengal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The Andaman and the Nicobar Islands lie to the southeast of the Indian mainland in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41); font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Bay of Bengal.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Andaman and Nicobar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;Islands is&amp;nbsp;a union territory in&amp;nbsp;India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are a total of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;572 islands&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;Andaman and Nicobar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Port Blair&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the territorial capital of Andaman and Nicobar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Andaman in the south is separated from the Nicobar Islands by the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Ten Degree Channel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Andaman and Nicobar were earlier known as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Emerald islands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Onch, Jarawa, Sentinelis&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;etc are the major tribal peoples of&amp;nbsp;Andaman and Nicobar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Barren Island&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the only active volcano in&amp;nbsp;Andaman and Nicobar.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The British captured&amp;nbsp;Andaman and Nicobar in 1872.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Lakshadweep&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the smallest union territory of India.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is situated in the Arabian sea.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Maldives is the country lying nearest to&amp;nbsp;Lakshadweep.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Minicoy&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an island in Lakshadweep.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Minicoy is also known as &amp;quot;island without crow&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Amindiv&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an island in Lakshadweep.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Formerly Lakshadweep was known as Laccadive, Minicoy, and Amindivi Islands,&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
